eview historical maintenance records for prior insulation degradation trends', 'Check for loose or corroded connections at the star point'], 'observations': ['Megger test shows insulation resistance < 0.5M ohms to ground (confirmed ground fault)', 'Motor terminal box inspection reveals severe carbon tracking and flashover damage on star point connections', 'No evidence of external contamination or moisture ingress in the terminal box', 'Star point connections exhibit signs of overheating and partial melting'], 'rectification': ['Step 1: Isolate and lock out the motor per LOTO procedures', 'Step 2: Disassemble and clean the terminal box, removing all carbonized insulation and damaged components', 'Step 3: Replace the star point connections with new, high-temperature-rated terminals and insulation materials', 'Step 4: Rewind or repair the stator windings if damage extends beyond the terminal box (assess via surge comparison test)', 'Step 5: Apply conformal coating to repaired areas to prevent future moisture ingress', 'Step 6: Perform post-repair Megger and hipot tests to verify insulation integrity (minimum 1000V DC, >100M ohms resistance)', 'Step 7: Reassemble the terminal box and reconnect the motor, ensuring all connections are torqued to specification']}
